{"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"content","content":[{"text":"Overview","type":"heading","anchor":"Overview","level":2},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"The UI product layers three view modifiers on top of "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"RevenueCatUI"},{"type":"text","text":". Two primitives present the paywall and customer center directly from a "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Binding<Bool>"},{"type":"text","text":"; one convenience modifier composes both, driven by "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallState"},{"type":"text","text":". Each presentation modifier attaches to the modified content view directly — there are no "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"View"},{"type":"text","text":" wrappers and no "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".background { … }"},{"type":"text","text":" indirection. This shape is what makes the macOS sheet machinery present reliably."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"For step-by-step wiring, see "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"How to Present the UI"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" in the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"},{"text":" documentation. For the rationale behind platform-specific behavior, see ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Platform Behavior"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" in the same catalog.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"anchor":"Library-target","text":"Library target","level":2,"type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Product: "},{"code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Import: "},{"code":"import SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI","type":"codeVoice"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Package.swift"},{"type":"text","text":":"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"codeListing","code":[".product(name: \"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI\", package: \"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\"),"],"syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The UI product depends on ","type":"text"},{"code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"RevenueCatUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", both pulled in transitively. Apps that don’t ship paywall UI in the same target (for example, a tests-only target) can depend on the lower-level ","type":"text"},{"code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" product alone.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"type":"heading","anchor":"Modifiers","text":"Modifiers","level":2},{"type":"heading","anchor":"revenueCatPaywallisPresentedofferingIdentifierdisplayCloseButtononDismiss","text":"`revenueCatPaywall(isPresented:offeringIdentifier:displayCloseButton:onDismiss:)`","level":3},{"code":["extension View {","    public func revenueCatPaywall(","        isPresented: Binding<Bool>,","        offeringIdentifier: String? = nil,","        displayCloseButton: Bool = true,","        onDismiss: (() -> Void)? = nil","    ) -> some View","}"],"type":"codeListing","syntax":"swift"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Attaches "},{"code":"RevenueCatUI.PaywallView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" as a platform-appropriate sheet."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"iOS","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — Presents in a "},{"code":"fullScreenCover","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" so the paywall takes the full screen."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"macOS","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — Presents in a "},{"code":"sheet","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" sized to a 400×600 minimum."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Pass a real two-way binding; SwiftUI sets it to ","type":"text"},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" on user dismissal. Build it from ","type":"text"},{"code":"PaywallState.isPresented","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" so the ","type":"text"},{"code":"set:","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" closure dispatches ","type":"text"},{"code":".paywall(.dismiss)","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and the plugin clears its presentation state.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":4,"text":"Parameters","anchor":"Parameters","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"isPresented","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" — Two-way binding to the paywall’s visibility flag."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"offeringIdentifier","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" — Identifier of the RevenueCat offering to present, for a win-back or regional offer. Defaults to "},{"code":"nil","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":", which presents the dashboard’s current offering. An unknown identifier or a failed fetch falls back to the current offering with a logged warning."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"displayCloseButton","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" — Whether "},{"code":"PaywallView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" shows a close button. Defaults to "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". Neither the iOS "},{"code":"fullScreenCover","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" nor the macOS "},{"code":"sheet","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" offers any other dismissal affordance, so pass "},{"code":"false","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" only for a hard paywall the user must purchase through."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"onDismiss","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" — Optional callback fired after dismissal."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":3,"text":"`revenueCatCustomerCenter(isPresented:onDismiss:)`","anchor":"revenueCatCustomerCenterisPresentedonDismiss","type":"heading"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["extension View {","    public func revenueCatCustomerCenter(","        isPresented: Binding<Bool>,","        onDismiss: (() -> Void)? = nil","    ) -> some View","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Attaches the customer center as a platform-appropriate sheet.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"iOS","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — Presents "},{"code":"RevenueCatUI.CustomerCenterView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" in a "},{"code":"sheet","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"type":"strong","inlineContent":[{"text":"macOS","type":"text"}]},{"type":"text","text":" — Opens "},{"code":"itms-apps:\/\/apps.apple.com\/account\/subscriptions","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" via "},{"code":"NSWorkspace.shared.open","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" (falling back to the "},{"code":"https:\/\/apps.apple.com\/account\/subscriptions","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" web URL if nothing on the system handles the "},{"code":"itms-apps","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" scheme), immediately clears the binding, and fires "},{"code":"onDismiss","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":". RevenueCatUI does not ship a customer center on macOS."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":4,"text":"Parameters","anchor":"Parameters","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"isPresented"},{"type":"text","text":" — Two-way binding to the customer center’s visibility flag."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"onDismiss","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" — Optional callback fired after dismissal (or, on macOS, after the App Store URL is opened).","type":"text"}]}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":3,"text":"`revenueCatPaywall(state:offeringIdentifier:displayCloseButton:send:)`","anchor":"revenueCatPaywallstateofferingIdentifierdisplayCloseButtonsend","type":"heading"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["extension View {","    public func revenueCatPaywall(","        state: PaywallState,","        offeringIdentifier: String? = nil,","        displayCloseButton: Bool = true,","        send: @escaping (PaywallAction) -> Void","    ) -> some View","}"]},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Convenience modifier that attaches both "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"revenueCatPaywall(isPresented:offeringIdentifier:displayCloseButton:onDismiss:)"},{"type":"text","text":" and "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"revenueCatCustomerCenter(isPresented:onDismiss:)"},{"type":"text","text":" and dispatches the matching dismiss action when each sheet closes."}],"type":"paragraph"},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The two presentations are mutually exclusive; the paywall wins. While ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"state.isPresented"},{"text":" is ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"true"},{"text":" the customer-center binding reads ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"false"},{"text":", and a request for either surface while the other is up dispatches ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":".dismissCustomerCenter"},{"text":" — the platform refuses simultaneous presentations, and this rule keeps ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallState"},{"text":" from holding a flag the platform ignored. See ","type":"text"},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"Platform Behavior"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"text":" in the ","type":"text"},{"code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" documentation.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"},{"level":4,"text":"Parameters","anchor":"Parameters","type":"heading"},{"items":[{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"state","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" — The paywall slice from your store, typically ","type":"text"},{"code":"store.paywall","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"codeVoice","code":"offeringIdentifier"},{"type":"text","text":" — Identifier of the RevenueCat offering to present. Defaults to "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"nil"},{"type":"text","text":" (the dashboard’s current offering); see the primitive modifier above."}]}]},{"content":[{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"code":"displayCloseButton","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" — Whether "},{"code":"PaywallView","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" shows a close button. Defaults to "},{"code":"true","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":"; see the primitive modifier above.","type":"text"}]}]},{"content":[{"inlineContent":[{"code":"send","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" — A closure that lifts a "},{"code":"PaywallAction","type":"codeVoice"},{"type":"text","text":" into your root action and dispatches it through the store. Typically "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"{ store.send(.paywall($0)) }"},{"type":"text","text":"."}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"type":"unorderedList"},{"level":4,"text":"Equivalent manual wiring","anchor":"Equivalent-manual-wiring","type":"heading"},{"syntax":"swift","type":"codeListing","code":["ContentView()","    .revenueCatPaywall(","        isPresented: Binding(","            get: { store.paywall.isPresented },","            set: { if !$0 { store.send(.paywall(.dismiss)) } }","        )","    )","    .revenueCatCustomerCenter(","        isPresented: Binding(","            get: { store.paywall.isCustomerCenterPresented },","            set: { if !$0 { store.send(.paywall(.dismissCustomerCenter)) } }","        )","    )"]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"Use the convenience modifier when both sheets are needed; use the primitives when only one is needed or when you want to interleave other modifiers between them.","type":"text"}],"type":"paragraph"}]}],"variants":[{"paths":["\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/uicomponentsreference"],"traits":[{"interfaceLanguage":"swift"}]}],"identifier":{"url":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/UIComponentsReference","interfaceLanguage":"swift"},"hierarchy":{"paths":[["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"]]},"sections":[],"kind":"article","seeAlsoSections":[{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPresentTheUI","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/PlatformBehavior"],"anchor":"Related-Documentation","title":"Related Documentation"},{"identifiers":["doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/ServiceReference","doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/MockServiceReference"],"anchor":"Reference","generated":true,"title":"Reference"}],"metadata":{"role":"article","title":"UI Components Reference","modules":[{"name":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall"}],"roleHeading":"Article"},"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"major":0,"minor":3},"abstract":[{"text":"API reference for the ","type":"text"},{"code":"revenueCatPaywall","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"code":"revenueCatCustomerCenter","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" view modifiers — the SwiftUI surface of ","type":"text"},{"code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"references":{"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/PlatformBehavior":{"type":"topic","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/PlatformBehavior","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/platformbehavior","abstract":[{"text":"Why the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"revenueCatPaywall"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"revenueCatCustomerCenter"},{"text":" modifiers present differently on iOS and macOS, and what is hard-coded.","type":"text"}],"title":"Platform Behavior"},"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall":{"type":"topic","role":"collection","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall","kind":"symbol","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall","title":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall","abstract":[{"text":"RevenueCat adapter for Swidux’s ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallPlugin"},{"type":"text","text":". Implements "},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallService"},{"type":"text","text":" against "},{"code":"Purchases.shared","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":", ships a controllable mock for previews and tests, and pairs with ","type":"text"},{"code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" for drop-in ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallView"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"CustomerCenterView"},{"type":"text","text":" presentation."}]},"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/MockServiceReference":{"url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/mockservicereference","title":"Mock Service Reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/MockServiceReference","kind":"article","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"API reference for ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"MockRevenueCatPaywallService"},{"text":" — a controllable ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallService"},{"text":" conformer for previews and tests that does not touch ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"Purchases.shared"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"role":"article"},"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/HowToPresentTheUI":{"type":"topic","role":"article","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/HowToPresentTheUI","kind":"article","url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/howtopresenttheui","abstract":[{"text":"Attach the ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"revenueCatPaywall"},{"text":" and ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"revenueCatCustomerCenter"},{"text":" view modifiers from ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"SwiduxRevenueCatPaywallUI"},{"text":" to a root view, driven by ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"PaywallState"},{"text":".","type":"text"}],"title":"How to Present the UI"},"doc://SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/documentation/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall/ServiceReference":{"url":"\/documentation\/swiduxrevenuecatpaywall\/servicereference","title":"Service Reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/documentation\/SwiduxRevenueCatPaywall\/ServiceReference","kind":"article","type":"topic","abstract":[{"text":"API reference for ","type":"text"},{"code":"RevenueCatPaywallService","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" — the RevenueCat-backed ","type":"text"},{"code":"PaywallService","type":"codeVoice"},{"text":" conformer that the paywall plugin consumes.","type":"text"}],"role":"article"}}}